74. Outline the file reading and writing functions of PHP with suitable examples.
code:
<?php
// Open file for writing
$file = fopen("sample.txt", "w");

// Write content
fwrite($file, "Hello World!\nThis is a test file.");

// Close file
fclose($file);

// Using file_put_contents
file_put_contents("sample2.txt", "Hello again!");

// Output message
echo "Files written successfully.";
?>
